<br>
Shammy is extremely boring until level 24. Gets TONS more fun after that. Great solo class and very welcome in groups. A very straight forward class that you can have tons of fun with in the higher levels.<br>
<br>
Gnome's as a race, are one of the &quot;most tolerated&quot; in EQ. Am agnostic gnome can walk into just about any city in EQ. I'll let yo u find out which ones you are KoS in =). Keep in mind, as you gain the ability to cast illusions, your race ** almost ** becomes irrelevant. Gnomes also may not have the best stats for an enchanter but are probably the most fun to roleplay =).<br>
<br>
Enchanters are almost always welcome in groups. Perhaps not in the lower levels but certainly as you gain in power and skill you will almost always be able to get a group. Chanters can do more than just charm when soloing. A few tactics you can use to solo are:<br>
<br>
1. Agro kite - Generate tons of agro (tash / nukes) , make sure you have sow / jboots, and run around with your pet smacking the mob behind you. More effective now with the recent pet changes and in old world zones. Not very effective past level 35 as mobs start to get to many HP.<br>
<br>
2. Chain cast your invuln line - Summon your pet and chain cast (as needed) your re-agentless invuln spells on your pet. Can't recall when you get these spells, but they are spread all over. Very effective once you slow your target and just sit and med up inbetween casts. I still do this from time to time.<br>
<br>
3. Charm - Always good to pick your targets (and pet) carefully. Keep targets rooted. Toss in a nuke here and there if need be. A nice trick to do is to let both your target and your pet get beaten up so by the time your pet wins, its really low health. Then break charm and kill your former pet for xp.<br>
<br>
Have fun! <p>Kzan Verto<BR>
